<item>
            <title>[SHDP-126] Distcp.copy(Boolean preserveReplication,..., String... uris) throws away arguments</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SHDP-126</link>
                <project id="10801" key="SHDP">Spring for Apache Hadoop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The DistCp.copy() that has booleans is incomplete.&lt;br/&gt;
It builds an arglist but only adds the arguments from the &quot;preserveReplication&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
argument to the &quot;delete&quot; argument and doesn&apos;t include:&lt;br/&gt;
Long fileLimit, Long sizeLimit, String fileList, String... uris&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The use of this method results in:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Missing dst path&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Two other versions of DistCp.copy() are affected by this also, since both&lt;br/&gt;
call the one with the bug in it: They are the the ones having EnumSet&amp;lt;Preserve&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
as the first argument.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workaround: use the DistCp.copy(String... args) versions&lt;/p&gt;</description>
